4:
My first memory is of light,
surrounded by voices.
5:
A hand caressed my cheek as notes
of sorrow filled my ears...
6:
The high elves chanted, begging for
hope to rescue them from despair.
13:
A high elf born in this very forest...
Yes, I had heard of thisâ€”but I do not
recall when.
14: What do you seek from me?
18:
You shall soon reach the end of your
life.
21:
Out of all the beings in this forest, 
it is you who most reeks of death.
23:
I have come to witness your passing
and learn from it.
26:
Little princess, why do you wish to
learn of death?
29: To shatter the illusion of eternity.
35:
The high elves fear the loss of
eternity.
38:
More and more elves are starless,
afflicted with mortality. The high
elves view this as an ill omen, but
they are cowards.
41:
I believe differently. Mortality is what
allows for living beings to change
and grow.
43:
Yet you are a high elf yourself,
immortal...
46:
That is why I have come to learn of
death. From you.
48: Haha... Very well. Do what you wish.
50:
Watch over my final moments, if
that is what you truly desire.
54: Do you not fear the coming end?
56:
Dragons are offered as sacrifices to
the Purger, though I've heard not all
are content to accept this fate.
57:
Are you different? Or are you
another coward of the forest,
deluding yourself inside a dream?
62:
Even if I am no longer a youthful
dragon, roaring with rage and fire... 
I do still fear death.
63:
But there is something I fear even
more.
66: And what could that possibly be?
69: Seeing all that I love fade away...
70:
Alas, I have a duty to remain here. 
I can do nothing but wait.
78:
Then I will lend you my power, so
that you may live to see your duty
through.
81:
But if destiny doesn't smile upon
you, then I will receive your Mark.
84:
Is that... possible? The Mark is meant
for the Purger's sword.
87:
If we use the forest's energy to
extend your life and combine our
powers, it should be.
92:
You certainly are insatiable. Very
well. Speak it.
95:
I wish to converse with you more
often, from this day forward.
98:
I need to learn all I can about death,
and what it is like to face it.
100:
To shatter the illusion of eternity. 
I must.
103:
That is agreeable. Witness my end,
as you require.
118:
Yes... Of the day we met. It was very...
nostalgic...
122:
Nostalgic, hm? Surely a few years is
but a blink of an eye to you.
125:
Not at all... But even if it were, I would
struggle to forget that memory...
129:
The flame of my life grows dim... But
it is thanks to you that I was able to
fulfill my duty.
131:
I am forever in your debt, little
princess.
137: I shall go do my duty, as I swore.
139:
We will see if I am worthy to carry on
your legacy.
142:
The high elves are lost in grief,
lamenting the ever-continuing birth
of mortal elves.
145:
I don't intend to join them in their
mourning.
147:
Would it not be easier to lose
yourself in a dream as well?
153:
I am the Paragon of Hope. Come
death or destruction, I will keep my
promise to you.
159:
Perhaps I should not wish for this...
But nonetheless, I pray...
160:
For this world I love to endure... And
that the princess may live to see
tomorrow...
